	$LF
]p
[p 
	[a class=extlink href=http://i.imgur.com/mt6S1oj rel=nofollow 
		"This image
	]a
	" shows where exactly the player supposedly died. In case the image becomes defunct: After the middle area, the player died between the 2nd cloud and the 4.5th cloud. 
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The game seems to depend on address $FFE5 (X-Cam related) when choosing where Mario should respawn and in the above case, the player should normally have been placed to a checkpoint prior to the one where he was put (= at the end). If this occurence can be reproduced in a timely manner, it will save time in a speedrun and TAS. 
	[br 
	]br
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	" 
	[a class=extlink href=http://www.speedrun.com/sml1/thread/hxo41 rel=nofollow 
		"Source
	]a
	" (The posts by the finder do not exist anymore, for some reason. I have a copy of the page with all the finder's messages intact. I will upload it by request.)
	$LF
