[h2 
	" Guide
	$LF
	[a id=heading-6006 
	]a
]h2
[p 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Should a never-before seen glitch happen to you, please provide the following information in your report:
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"System
	]b
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	" What system did you play on? 
	[br 
	]br
	" What region of the system (PAL, NTSC)? 
	[br 
	]br
	" If you used an emulator, which one was it? Which version of it (Look in the About section)?
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Game version
	]b
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	" Which version of the game do you have? 
	[br 
	]br
	" Gather information what versions there are in the first place - Look at GameFAQs (their release information shows you where the game has been released). Most often, games are separated between US, Europe and Japan. 
	[br 
	]br
	" Which revision of the game do you have? 
	[br 
	]br
	" This is the case only for some games. Ask around if your game has revisions (such as Super Mario Land v1.0 and v1.1). Consult 
	[a class=extlink href=http://tcrf.net rel=nofollow 
		"The Cutting Room Floor
	]a
	" for information on version differences.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Information
	]b
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	" What is the bug that happened? Explain it with as much detail as possible. 
	[br 
	]br
	" What did you do before it happened? 
	[br 
	]br
	" Where exactly did it happen? Provide a screenshot and mark exactly where it happened. 
	[br 
	]br
	" If you are unable to take a screenshot, look up existing maps such as the ones on 
	[a class=extlink href=http://VGMaps.com rel=nofollow 
		"VGMaps
	]a
	", download them and mark where it happened, then upload them and link them.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[br 
	]br
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]p
